                  </hi>. I am a carman, of 5, Montague Place, Whitechapel—on Saturday, 4th December, I bought a pawn-ticket of the prisoner for 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., with which I took the great-coat out of pawn—he first offered it to me on Thursday, 2nd December—my mate and I both wanted it—I had not got the money then, but I bought it on Saturday night—I had to pay the pawnbroker 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—the prosecutor identified the coat.</p>
